Date: Wed, 04 Mar 2009 11:49:36
From: Juan Zhou [jnuzhoujuan@126.com]
Subject: International Conference on Modern Chinese Grammar

E-mail this message to a friend:
http://linguistlist.org/issues/emailmessage/verification.cfm?iss=20-682.html&submissionid=207507&topicid=3&msgnumber=1
  

Full Title: International Conference on Modern Chinese Grammar 

Date: 28-Nov-2009 - 30-Nov-2009
Location: The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hong Kong 
Contact Person: Juan Zhou
Meeting Email: jnuzhoujuan@126.com

Linguistic Field(s): Semantics; Syntax 

Call Deadline: 15-Apr-2009 

Meeting Description:

The Fifth International Conference on Modern Chinese Grammar will be held at 
The Hong Kong Polytechnic University on November 28-30, 2009 and abstracts on 
any aspect of the grammar of Modern Chinese are invited. 

Call for Papers

Abstracts could be written in Chinese or English and should be limited to one A4
page. Please send 2 hard copies of the abstract (one with the author's name and
affiliation, and one without) to Ms. Zhou Juan, c/o the Organizing Committee of
the Fifth International Conference on Modern Chinese Grammar, at Department of
Chinese, Ji'nan University, Guangzhou, P. R. China (Zip code: 510632) by postal
mail, and an e-copy to the following e-mail address: jnuzhoujuan@126.com on or
before April 15, 2009. Abstract selection is based on anonymous review.

Young scholars may apply for the competitive scholarships provided by the
organizing committee. Postgraduate students and recent graduates whose rank is
below Associate Professor are eligible to apply. Applicants should submit two
hard copies of full paper to the organizing committee (one with the author's
name and contact address, and one without) on or before April 15, 2009.

Notifications of (non)acceptance will be sent off in early July, 2009. Please
contact Ms. Zhou Juan by email at jnuzhoujuan@126.com for inquiries.



	
